<br>
1 - Remove the Level 49 cap on the Solusek Ro items.<br>
<br>
2 - Impliment a quest for the 44+ Magician market to combine all 4 Solusek Ro foci into the above weapon. EG: NPC in Sol Ro gives you a box with 4 spaces. You must get it imbued by 4 other wandering Magicians (Akistaff in Najena and Walna in BBM could be 2). All these mages require a monetary fee since platinum dust is needed as the spell component. Say 200pp per person. Then you put your 4 foci into the container and hit combine. You recieve the message &quot;You lacked the skill to create somethign new&quot;, freak out and realise an item on your cursor. It identifies as &quot;Mangled elements&quot;. You then hand this back to the Sol Ro NPC and he/she fashions the mess into the Staff of Elemental Flux (my madeup item) for another fee of maybe 500pp. &lt;hey, why can't I have fun quests??&gt;<br>
<br>
3 - Up the level effect of the Elemental Mastery Staves and impliment above quest for the staves too!<br>
<br>
4 - Allow both quest pieces to be combined into the uber-foci for Magicians! And give the Orb of Mastery the same effect <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uodibillauxes.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Odibil Lauxes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 37<br> <font color=#333333>(5/17/02 1:02:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=201.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sunglasses.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Details...</span><hr size=1> I'll agree with number four.<br>
<br>
I also believe the Orb of Mastery should possess the same focus modifiers as the four elemental staves combined.<br>
<br>
I base this on the fact that nobody in their right mind would possess any focus item aside from the fire staff, unless they were quite greedy, or very fortunate.<br>
<br>
The quest involved for the air staff is ridiculous, as the crown required is used as a part of our epic, which is not a walk in the park to obtain. Both the earth and water staves are also used as a part of our epic, and very rarely will anyone possess a second staff that is not going to be multiquested away at one point, unless they are privileged enough to do so.<br>
<br>
So in essence, you're giving up all of your focus items to concentrate the power into the Orb of Mastery, and all attributes of those focus items should still remain in the orb. <p><br><center><font face="tahoma, verdana" size="1">[ <b>Baron</b> | <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=90407" target="blank">Odibil Lauxes</a> | <b>Arch Mage</b> ]<br>Pain and Suffering tries to strike YOU, but misses!</font></center></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#333333>- </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower>The Magician's Tower</a><font color=#333333> - </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32>Class Balance</a> <font color=#333333> - </font><a href="http://www.magecompendium.com/">The Mage Compendium</a><font color=#333333> - </font>  <br><br><table border=0 align=center><tr><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">Upgrade your account to ezSupporter...</a></td><td><img src="http://www.ezboard.com/image/spacer.gif" width=15 height=1 border=0></td><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">...and never see another ad or pop-up again</a></td></tr></table><CENTER><!-- START BOTTOM AD SCRIPT -->
